Substituting this into the inequality, it suffices to show $\sum_{i,j} (1 - \cos(t(x_i - x_j))) \le \sum_{i,j} (1 - \cos(t(x_i + x_j)))$ for all $t > 0$, or equivalently $\sum_{i,j} \cos(t(x_i + x_j)) \le \sum_{i,j} \cos(t(x_i - x_j))$.
Using trigonometric identities, the RHS is $|\sum_k e^{itx_k}|^2 = (\sum \cos(tx_k))^2 + (\sum \sin(tx_k))^2$, and the LHS is $\text{Re}((\sum e^{itx_k})^2) = (\sum \cos(tx_k))^2 - (\sum \sin(tx_k))^2$.
